102OTVYpILjvAhnvIeUdlZBP9YI2sjs3htWbvNYqQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing H2 in Gradle**\\n\\nI’m working on configuring Gradle to dynamically find the H2 jar in the test runtime classpath. This involves setting up a task to prepare the exploded H2 runtime by checking for the existence of the H2 jar file, which is critical. If it’s not found, I need to throw a Gradle exception. Then, I’ll copy the relevant files while excluding unnecessary content — and ensure the process is efficient. Let’s see how it all pulls together!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Z4y8m6HvgVtrTdNlVyxZef0R|fc_01ec786bdc7a64a00169f102ea3c1881a1a623419001678fdf", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\ndependencies {\n\ttestImplementation(\"com.h2database:h2:$libraryVersion\")\n\ttestImplementation(\"org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0\")\n}\n\ntest {\n    systemProperty 'h2.javaObjectSerializer', 'h2.JdbcUtilsTest$PassThroughJavaObjectSerializer'\n}\n", "newText": "String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\nProvider<Directory> explodedH2Runtime = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\"exploded-h2-runtime\")\n\nTaskProvider<Task> prepareExplodedH2Runtime = tasks.register(\"prepareExplodedH2Runtime\") { task ->\n    task.inputs.files(configurations.testRuntimeClasspath)\n    task.outputs.dir(explodedH2Runtime)\n    task.doLast {\n        File h2Jar = configurations.testRuntimeClasspath.files.find { file ->\n            file.name == \"h2-${libraryVersion}.jar\"\n        }\n        if (h2Jar == null) {\n            throw new GradleException(\"Unable to locate h2-${libraryVersion}.jar on the test runtime classpath\")\n        }\n        File outputDir = explodedH2Runtime.get().asFile\n        delete(outputDir)\n        copy {\n            from(zipTree(h2Jar)) {\n                exclude \"org/h2/util/data.zip\"\n            }\n            into(outputDir)\n        }\n        copy {\n            from(zipTree(h2Jar)) {\n                include \"org/h2/util/data.zip\"\n            }\n            into(task.temporaryDir)\n        }\n        copy {\n            from(zipTree(new File(task.temporaryDir, \"org/h2/util/data.zip\")))\n            into(outputDir)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\ndependencies {\n\ttestImplementation(\"com.h2database:h2:$libraryVersion\")\n\ttestImplementation(\"org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0\")\n}\n\ntest {\n    systemProperty 'h2.javaObjectSerializer', 'h2.JdbcUtilsTest$PassThroughJavaObjectSerializer'\n    dependsOn prepareExplodedH2Runtime\n    classpath = files(explodedH2Runtime).builtBy(prepareExplodedH2Runtime) + classpath.filter { file ->\n        file.name != \"h2-${libraryVersion}.jar\"\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2243, "output": 1593, "cacheRead": 70656, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 74492, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777402586737, "responseId": "resp_01ec786bdc7a64a00169f102dbaa2881a180bfc1817a1978c0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Z4y8m6HvgVtrTdNlVyxZef0R|fc_01ec786bdc7a64a00169f102ea3c1881a1a623419001678fdf", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/build.gradle."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n  9 }\n 10 \n 11 String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n 12 \n+13 Provider<Directory> explodedH2Runtime = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\"exploded-h2-runtime\")\n+14 \n+15 TaskProvider<Task> prepareExplodedH2Runtime = tasks.register(\"prepareExplodedH2Runtime\") { task ->\n+16     task.inputs.files(configurations.testRuntimeClasspath)\n+17     task.outputs.dir(explodedH2Runtime)\n+18     task.doLast {\n+19         File h2Jar = configurations.testRuntimeClasspath.files.find 